      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That \"dead soil\" feeling is likely a nutrient sponge phenomenon, where unscrupulous soil tie-ups or compacted dirt prevent roots from accessing what's available. Over time, some intense cultivation can exhaust the mycorrhizal fungi crucial for root health, basically starving the plant underground. The imbalance is often microbial, meaning good bacteria that \"unlock\" nutrients are outnumbered by less helpful species. Adding some rich, composted organic matter can reintroduce the healthy life force back into your blueberry beds.",
